        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Hardened runtime/plugin schema and metadata boundaries so malformed or unreadable synthetic plugin data is quarantined, omitted, or treated as absent instead of crashing assistant startup, doctor/setup flows, provider selection, channel authorization, Codex app-server routing, gateway startup planning, native approval routing, SDK helper APIs, provider tool-schema compatibility traversal, or outbound message action handling.\n- Kept test fixtures synthetic: current test content uses `fuzzplugin`, `mockplugin`, and `fuzz_move_*` names rather than the reported third-party plugin name.\n- Added follow-up hardening for outbound structured attachment params, outbound JSON params (`presentation`, `delivery`, `interactive`), `runMessageAction` input param copying, exported message action normalization/target-spec helpers, exported message action threading controls/writes, and plugin SDK provider-tool descriptors.\n- Provider tool compatibility helpers now guard the tool descriptor itself, so unreadable `name`, unreadable `parameters`, and normalized-copy traps omit or diagnose the bad synthetic tool instead of crashing schema normalization.\n\n## Linked context\n\nWhich issue does this close?\n\nNo linked closing issue.\n\nWhich issues, PRs, or discussions are related?\n\nNo linked related issue.\n\nWas this requested by a maintainer or owner?\n\nMaintainer-directed hardening/debugging work.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: malformed runtime plugin tool schemas and hostile plugin/config/provider/manifest/native-approval/outbound-action metadata can crash or widen decisions before normal OpenClaw diagnostics, setup, provider routing, gateway startup planning, approval forwarding, message action validation, provider tool-schema compatibility traversal, or Codex app-server handling complete.\n\nReal environment tested: local focused Vitest through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`; broad remote validation on direct AWS Crabbox Linux runners because Blacksmith Testbox auth was unavailable in this shell.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n- Direct pre/post `tsx` repros for unreadable synthetic provider tool descriptors: unreadable `parameters`, unreadable `name`, and own-key traps during normalized tool copy no longer throw raw errors.\n- Direct pre/post `tsx` repros for synthetic message action threading writes, unreadable threading controls, message action normalization params, runner params, provider wizard metadata, manifest channel metadata, native approval approver iterators, shared action params, structured attachments, and JSON action params.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugin-sdk/provider-tools.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (1 file / 15 tests)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.threading.test.ts --reporter=verbose` (1 file / 24 tests)\n- Earlier focused batches for outbound normalization/params, shared action params, provider auth/onboarding, manifest/tool availability, channel/config fixtures, Codex image payloads, and fuzz guard type/lint drift.\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check` and `node_modules/.bin/oxlint` on the latest touched file sets.\n- `git diff --check`\n- Added-line scrub for reported plugin names, local paths, and private network literals.\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local --base refs/remotes/origin/main`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base refs/remotes/origin/main`\n- `node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --idle-timeout 90m --ttl 240m --timing-json --shell -- \"pnpm check:changed\"`\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- Latest local autoreview on the provider-tool descriptor slice: clean with no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Latest focused proof after rebase to `f7b0b5429e`: `provider-tools.test.ts` passed 1 file / 15 tests; oxfmt, oxlint, `git diff --check`, and added-line scrub passed.\n- `origin/main` advanced repeatedly with zero touched-path overlap through `1901b832eb`, `3a20a0cd4f`, `5cccfe1c17`, `c903b271cf`, `091e15139b`, `61c538e2fc`, `8bd4736f03`, and `f7b0b5429e`; the branch rebased cleanly through those tips.\n- AWS Crabbox changed gate after the provider-wizard slice: provider `aws`, lease `cbx_991a8c29acdf`, run `run_41811346ac17`, command `pnpm check:changed`, exit 0 on base `8e806e9125`.\n- Earlier AWS Crabbox changed gate for the branch: provider `aws`, lease `cbx_52b1fe398bd3`, run `run_c85914033aaa`, command `pnpm check:changed`, exit 0 over core, coreTests, extensions, and extensionTests.\n- Current branch head after rebase/push: `a9bdacc26fcaab7786623e948b753c302ab0398d`.\n- Current PR base observed after the latest rebase proof: `f7b0b5429efed34f6dac0b157e09452850afa178`.\n- Current test/source/docs scrub: no reported third-party plugin name remains in checked repo content for this branch.\n\nObserved result after fix:\n\n- Hostile synthetic config/schema/provider/manifest/native-approval/message-action inputs are bounded at the relevant owner boundary instead of throwing raw getter/enumeration/serialization/spread errors.\n- Provider tool-schema compatibility traversal now guards descriptor reads and normalized descriptor copies before inspecting provider-specific schema keywords.\n- Message action normalization, threading controls, threading writes, JSON params, structured attachments, and runner param copies now fail closed at the relevant boundary instead of raw-crashing on synthetic accessors.\n- Provider wizard setup choices, gateway startup manifest planning, native approval routing, manifest tool availability, Codex image payload handling, and embedded-agent schema-quarantine fixtures retain their previously proven behavior.\n\nWhat was not tested:\n\n- Blacksmith Testbox was not run because `blacksmith auth login` is required in this shell; direct AWS Crabbox was used for broad remote gates.\n- The latest broad Crabbox gate predates the newest outbound runner/normalization/threading/provider-tool slices; those slices have focused local proof and local autoreview.\n- GitHub PR checks are queued/running on the pushed head.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\nDid user-visible behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes.\n\nDid config, environment, or migration behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nNo new config surface. Existing malformed/unreadable config, manifest, provider, tool descriptor, or action inputs now fail closed or resolve as absent at bounded reads.\n\nDid security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change? (`Yes/No`)\n\nYes. Malformed or unreadable tool/provider/plugin/native-approval/action metadata is rejected, omitted, or quarantined earlier instead of crashing runtime paths or broadening access.\n\nWhat is the highest-risk area?\n\nOverly strict sanitation could omit a valid provider tool descriptor or outbound action parameter.\n\nHow is that risk mitigated?\n\nThe changes preserve readable sibling entries, fail closed only for route/control/identity/idempotency-style action params in the newest outbound slices, keep unreadable payload-only fields as absent, preserve numeric alias behavior, and use focused regressions plus broad AWS `check:changed` gates from earlier branch slices.\n\n## Current review state\n\nWhat is the next action?\n\nReview the draft PR at head `a9bdacc26fcaab7786623e948b753c302ab0398d`.\n\nWhat is still waiting on author, maintainer, CI, or external proof?\n\nGitHub CI is queued/running after the force-push. No local actionable autoreview findings remain. The next work slice should start by checking whether `main` moved again before editing.\n\nWhich bot or reviewer comments were addressed?\n\nLocal autoreview findings were addressed, including Codex URL-backed image-block preservation, provider wizard receiver handling, native approval false-positive target matching, shared param-reader silent truncation, message action `topLevel`/`idempotencyKey` fail-closed handling, numeric legacy-target preservation, gu